BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:7lvutPJlhfgMhVCfw0VeI
SUMMARY:Boren Banner Series: Camille Trautman
DTSTAMP:20260326T120755Z
DTSTART:20260326T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Every photograph is a reminder that the act of framing is never
	 neutral. In Camille Trautman’s first solo museum exhibition in their home
	town\, the Seattle-born Duwamish artist uses photography and video to chal
	lenge colonial narratives and counter Indigenous erasure. The exhibition p
	resents selections from their ongoing series The North American LCD—spectr
	al self-portraits staged in varied natural landscapes. Rooted in Trautman’
	s process of coming out as transgender\, the images show the artist’s body
	 partially obscured by large LCD screens. The series examines how both lan
	dscape photography and digital media can shape or distort cultural identit
	y\, often by promoting or denying visibility.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.
	com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camille-trautman/16813305/2026-03
	-26T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camil
	le-trautman/16813305/2026-03-26T00
LOCATION:Frye Art Museum\, 704 Terry Ave\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT6H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3VoPJKh2M-X2rUnJSf422
SUMMARY:Scott Gibson - Visual Symphony II
DTSTAMP:20260326T120755Z
DTSTART:20260326T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:In March\, Visual Symphony II Scott Gibson invites viewers into
	 a world where music and art collide. Each work is an exploration of the v
	ivid\, sensory experience of sound translating into vibrant\, emotional vi
	suals. As an artist with synesthesia each work expresses Scott’s personal 
	perception of what music looks like. Scott uses resin techniques that he h
	as pioneered and pushes the boundaries of this medium.\n\nhttps://seatoday
	.6amcity.com/events/#/details/scott-gibson-visual-symphony-ii/18280602/202
	6-03-26T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/scott-gibson-visual-symph
	ony-ii/18280602/2026-03-26T00
LOCATION:Gray Sky Gallery\, 320 First Ave. S.\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT4H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Ys7oSz6fEQaMtcGG10uCJ
SUMMARY:Jazz Month Tour
DTSTAMP:20260326T120755Z
DTSTART:20260327T143000Z
DESCRIPTION:March’s Women in Jazz Month comes alive as award-winning singer
	-songwriter Eugenie Jones lights up the Royal Room with her national Women
	 in Jazz Month Tour. With stops in Denver\, San Francisco\, Atlanta\, and 
	Seattle\, this tour joins a worldwide tribute to the women who shaped jazz
	\, honoring trailblazers such as Billie Holiday\, Nina Simone\, and Ella F
	itzgerald. At the Royal Room\, Jones will blend beloved songs from female 
	jazz legends\, her own Jazz Week \\#4 ranked originals\, imaginative spins
	 on vintage jazz\, and timeless rhythm and blues classics. She’ll be joine
	d by the remarkable talents of pianist Peter Adams\, bassist Osama Afifi\,
	 and drummer Maria Wulff. As a Seattle Jazz Hall of Fame inductee\, the fi
	rst vocal recording artist to receive Earshot Jazz’s Album of the Year awa
	rd\, a two-time Vocalist of the Year winner\, and a Jazz Journalists Assoc
	iation’s Jazz Hero Award winner\, Jones has received high praise for her v
	ocal prowess. Paris Move magazine describes Jones as “One of the most beau
	tiful voices in the United States\; a consummate interpreter who slips eff
	ortlessly into the soul of her songs.” Preview Jones’ music\, watch videos
	\, or learn more about this gifted entertainer at  https://ffm.to/eugeniej
	onesmusic. Get your tickets today for this unforgettable night of exquisit
	e vocals\, masterful musicianship\, and stirring storytelling\, all in tri
	bute to the enduring legacy and vibrant contributions of women in jazz. Ti
	ckets:  https://www.strangertickets.com/events/180924339/eugenie-jones\n\n
	https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/jazz-month-tour/18252356/202
	6-03-27T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/jazz-month-tour/18252356/
	2026-03-27T00
LOCATION:The Royal Room\, 5000 Rainier Ave South\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
